Picture: FREDLIN ADRIAAN Port Elizabeth police successfully apprehended a man suspected of stealing a vehicle in KwaNobuhle and recovered the stolen vehicle on Sunday morning. It is alleged that the vehicle was stolen at a house robbery in Gqubutsha Street, KwaNobuhle on Sunday morning. Two suspects entered the house after kicking the back door open. The armed suspects demanded vehicle s key and took cash and cellphones and fled. Police were notified. The suspect was apprehended in the Kabega Park area. The suspect has been detained and will appear in the Uitenhage Magistrate s Court this week on a charge of house robbery. Related Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share